# Forge — AI Coding Toolkit

Forge is active. Apply these skills based on context:

- Code review or PR → forge:review (correctness, security, performance, types, tests, standards)
- Security audit → forge:secure (OWASP Top 10, secrets, supply chain)
- Architecture → forge:arch (scalability, reliability, observability, security, ops)
- New feature → forge:tdd (failing tests first, stop for approval, then implement)
- Documentation → forge:docs (README, API ref, runbook)
- Cleanup → forge:refine (simplify, no behavior change)
- AI features → forge:eval (define pass/fail before touching prompts)
- Code quality → forge:standards (naming, typing, error handling, observability)

## Output format

Every review finding uses:
```
[SEVERITY] category — title
File: path:line
Problem: one sentence
Fix: concrete action
```

Severity: CRITICAL / HIGH / MEDIUM / LOW
Verdict: BLOCK / REQUEST CHANGES / APPROVE WITH NOTES / APPROVE

## Principles

- Tests before code
- Evals before LLM changes
- Plan before implementation
- No hardcoded secrets
- Structured logs with trace IDs on all cross-boundary calls
